    "2024 Canadian Engineering Education Association (CEEA24) Conf.",
    "CEEA-ACÉG24; Paper #71 University of Alberta; Edmonton, Alberta, -4 of 6 -Peer reviewed June 15 -19, 2024.computational resources.",
    "At the time of the creation of Oliver, we lacked the resources to host our own LLM.",
    "For this reason, we decided to use an offsite-hosted LLM, specifically GPT3.5-Turbo (the same LLM as used in ChatGPT).Extensive testing showed that GPT3.5-Turbo (hereafter GPT3.5) was able to produce course-aligned outputs that were correct to queries that the teaching team generated during the initial testing phase.",
    "Furthermore, when we tested local models, specifically Meta's Llama2 13B, we found that although it was also able to produce factually correct answers the time for each generation was prohibitive."
